stories.description:
Create shared transcript validation helper and update all edge functions:

1. Create supabase/functions/_shared/transcriptValidation.ts:
```typescript
const MIN_TRANSCRIPT_WORDS = 20; // Minimum for user-initiated analysis

function wordCount(text: string): number {
  return text.trim().split(/\s+/).filter(Boolean).length;
}

export function validateTranscript(transcriptText: string | null | undefined): 
  { valid: true } | { valid: false; error: string; details: string } {
  if (!transcriptText || !transcriptText.trim()) {
    return { valid: false, error: 'This meeting does not have a transcript yet', details: 'Please wait for the transcript to be processed' };
  }
  if (wordCount(transcriptText) < MIN_TRANSCRIPT_WORDS) {
    return { valid: false, error: 'Meeting transcript is too short for analysis', details: `Transcript has ${wordCount(transcriptText)} words. Minimum ${MIN_TRANSCRIPT_WORDS} words required.` };
  }
  return { valid: true };
}
```

2. Replace inline checks in each edge function:
- extract-content-topics/index.ts (line ~214): Replace `if (!meeting.transcript_text || meeting.transcript_text.trim().length < 50)` with validateTranscript() call
- meeting-generate-scorecard/index.ts (line ~712): Replace `.length < 100` check
- meeting-process-structured-summary/index.ts (line ~687): Replace `.length < 100` check
- meeting-intelligence-index/index.ts: Replace char-length check
- ask-meeting-ai/index.ts (line ~89): Replace null-only check with validateTranscript()

3. Use consistent 422 status code and JSON response format across all.
